BNP PARIBAS OPEN
March 22, 2015
Vasek Pospisil
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT
 
 
  
 
  
  
   
 SOCK‑POSPISIL/Bolelli‑Fognini
  6‑4, 6‑7, 10‑7 
   
 Q.   How excited are you?  
VASEK POSPISIL:   Yeah, very happy, obviously.   Incredible week.   You know, we played well.   Every match we played great tennis.   It's just thrilling to end the week like that.   
Going to Miami with good confidence.  
   
 Q.   On the back of beating the Bryans, as well, just as you did in the Wimbledon final.   
VASEK POSPISIL:   Yeah, for sure, it makes it that much more special.   Obviously they are the best team in the world by far.   Greatest team in the history of the world.   
Any time you get a win on them, you know you're playing well and it's a great week.   Yeah, we are obviously thrilled with the way we have been playing.   
   
 Q.   Winning your first ATP Masters 1000 tournament, what does that mean?   
VASEK POSPISIL:   It's obviously another milestone.   Our first team title is probably can't be beat, you know, Wimbledon.   
But this is a Masters.   It's a huge event.   It's our first Masters title.   Hopefully you will we will have many more, but definitely a very good feeling.   
   
  
  
  
  
  

END_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT